🌑 UMBERHOLD: MASTER SPECIFICATION (.cursorrules)🛠️ I. CORE ARCHITECTURE (GODOT 4 / GDSCRIPT)Engine: Godot 4.x (Compatibility Renderer).Architecture: Strictly Modular & Decoupled. Systems must communicate via Signals/Events.Data Handling: Zero Hardcoding. All stats, items, and enemies must be loaded from JSON using Unique IDs.State Machine: Manage transitions between World_State (Exploration), Battle_State (Combat), and Menu_State.Save System: JSON persistence. Manual saves in cities; auto-saves on state transitions.Pathfinding: Use A* algorithm. Units can pass through allies (difficult terrain) but not enemies.Line of Sight: Use Bresenham’s Line Algorithm. Blocked by walls and mountains.UI Layout: Center Grid, Bottom Portraits (HP/AC), Right Text Log.👥 II. THE PARTY & STAT SYSTEM (3d8)Core Party: 4 Player-created units. If all 4 die = Game Over.Auxiliary: 2 slots for Summons/Mercs. Controlled by player; no inventory; permadeath.STR: Melee dmg, Carry weight (Capacity = $50 + (10 \times \text{STR})$).CON: HP, Poison resistance.AGI: AC, Initiative, Ranged accuracy.INT: Spell power, Identification.LCK: Crit range (19-20 if >15), Encounter avoidance.⚔️ III. COMBAT & ACTION ECONOMYGrid: 20x20 Tactical Grid. Orthogonal movement/melee.Initiative: $1d20 + \text{AGI bonus} + \text{Weapon Mod}$ (Light +2, Heavy -2).Turn: 1 Move (6 tiles) + 1 Action. Movement can be split.Actions: Attack, Cast Spell, Use Item, Swap Equipment.Free Actions: Drop item, Speak.Advantage/Disadvantage: Roll 2d20 (Take High/Low). Does not stack. Cancels out 1:1.Criticals: Natural 20 = Auto-hit + Double Damage Dice. Natural 1 = Auto-miss.Death: 0 HP = Instant Death. Core units leave a "Shadowy Skull" corpse.Resurrection: Requires Cleric/Phoenix Tear. Penalty: 1 HP, -4 to all d20 rolls (reduces by 1 per rest).🌑 IV. WORLD & VISIBILITY RULESCycle: 2h Day / 2h Night (Real-time). Affects visibility and encounter rates.Day Vision: Grass (10 tiles), Forest (3 tiles).Night Vision: Standard (2 tiles), Forest (1 tile). Torch adds +2.Encumbrance: 100% Load = -10ft move & Disadvantage on AGI. Overload = 0 movement.Encounters: Grass (5% per step), Forest/Night (15%).Loot Sacks: Dropped items persist on tile for 24 in-game hours.Win Condition: Collect 4 Elemental Sigils and defeat the "Void Architect."🎲 V. THE 14 MECHANICAL RULES (THE "LOGIC GATE")Advantage Cancellation: If both Adv/Disadv apply, roll 1d20 (regardless of quantity).Stat Scaling: Damage = Weapon Die + Stat Bonus.AC Calculation: $10 + \text{Armor} + \text{AGI}$ (AGI capped by heavy armor type).Spell Slots: Core units use 5e-style Slots; Aux units use Mana.Spell Saves: Target rolls vs. Caster DC ($8 + \text{INT} + \text{Proficiency}$).AoE Rules: Must have Line of Sight to the center tile of the effect.Status Ticks: Poison/Burn damage applies at the Start of the Unit's Turn.Poison Effect: $1d4$ dmg/turn + Disadvantage on all Attack rolls.Bleed Effect: $1d6$ dmg/turn; ends immediately if any healing is received.Equipment Swap: Costs 1 full Action.Inventory Stacking: Gold (100), Consumables (5), Equipment (None).AI Morale: Enemies check morale at 10% HP; if failed, they retreat/break.AI Priority: Attacks highest threat (last attacker) or lowest current HP.Corpse Loss: Leaving a corpse behind in a dungeon permanently deletes that character.